# API Contract Sync

`api-contract.md` is the human-readable contract reviewers read. It must match implemented routes.

## Trigger

When you **create, modify, or delete** any file under `src/backend/**/routers/` (or any `router*.py` registering endpoints), you **must** update `api-contract.md` in the same task — before marking work complete.

## Per-Endpoint Template

For each route, document:

```markdown
## Endpoint: <Short Name>

Method: <GET|POST|PATCH|DELETE>
Path: `/api/...`
Purpose: <one line>

### Request
<JSON body or query params with types>

### Response
<JSON shape with status codes>

### Validation Rules
<required fields, enums, auth requirement>

### Error Responses
<401, 403, 404, 422, invalid_status_transition, etc.>
```

## Ticket System Endpoints (expected)

| Method | Path | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| POST | `/api/auth/login` | Returns JWT |
| GET | `/api/tickets` | List + search/filter query params |
| POST | `/api/tickets` | Create; sets `createdBy` from JWT |
| GET | `/api/tickets/{id}` | Detail + comments |
| PATCH | `/api/tickets/{id}` | Update title, description, priority, assignee — **not status** |
| PATCH | `/api/tickets/{id}/status` | State machine only |
| POST | `/api/tickets/{id}/comments` | Add comment |
| GET | `/api/tickets/export` | CSV of caller's tickets |

Add rows when new routes appear; remove sections when routes are deleted.

## Sync Checklist

- [ ] Every router decorator has a matching `api-contract.md` section
- [ ] Request/response examples use real field names (`assignedTo`, `createdBy`, `ticketId`)
- [ ] Auth requirements stated (public vs Bearer JWT)
- [ ] Status transition errors documented on status endpoint
- [ ] `data-model.md` updated if payload shapes change

## Skill

Use the `sync-api-docs` skill for a structured sync pass.
